⚡ 8️⃣ Why This Is Powerful

✔ No class explosion
✔ Add features dynamically
✔ Follows Open/Closed Principle
✔ Flexible combinations

🧠 9️⃣ When to Use

✔ Add features dynamically
✔ Avoid subclass explosion
✔ Extend behavior without modifying class

🚫 🔟 When NOT to Use

Simple logic

No need for dynamic behavior

Too many small decorators (overkill)

